Roundware will run as the ubuntu user and group
I'd recommend moving all python packages into virtualenv to control versioning

INSTALL VIRTUALENV
1) sudo apt-get install virtualenvwrapper

2) log out of your current session and back in to source virtualenv startup file

3) create virtualenv
mkvirtualenv roundware

4) activate virtualenv
workon roundware

5) while in the virtualenv, re-install all required python packages
pip install -r /home/ubuntu/roundware-server/requirements.txt

SETUP APACHE TO USE WSGI
1) Install WSGI apache module
sudo apt-get install libapache2-mod-wsgi

2) Enable WSGI module
sudo a2enmode wsgi

3) Install roundware-apache config file
sudo ln -s /home/ubuntu/roundware-server/files/apache-config-example-wsgi /etc/apache2/sites-available/roundware

4) Enable roundware-apache config file
sudo a2ensite roundware

5) Restart apache
sudo service apache2 restart
